warningSetting.msg2.message: An alert will be issued when the class attendance rate is lower than the alert threshold

warningSetting.msg3.message: 1. If the attendance rate In a class roll call is lower than the alert threshold, an alert will be issued. If the attendance rate for multiple roll calls is lower than this value, multiple alerts will be issued.

warningSetting.msg4.message: 2. Changing the alert rules will not affect historical data, and the generated alert records will not be changed.

warningSetting.msg5.message: 3. A course being alerted only means that the attendance rate of the course needs the attention of the school administration and does not serve as a basis for the evaluation of teaching.

warningSetting.msg7.message: An alert will be issued to the student whose number of cumulative absences reaches the alert threshold

warningSetting.msg8.message: An alert will be issued to the student whose number of cumulative absences reaches the alert value. If the number of absences reaches 2 times or 3 times the early warning value, the second and third alerts will be issued.

warningSetting.msg9.message: 2. Changing the alert rules will not affect historical data, and the generated alert records will not be changed.
